Card Layout & Structure:
	•	Rounded rectangle card with soft shadow and subtle border
	•	Clean white or very light gray background
	•	Logo or icon at the top-left (agent / model / server logo)
	•	Card title in bold (Agent Name / Model Name / Service Name)
	•	Small provider label under the title (e.g., OpenAI, AWS, Internal, Meta)
	•	Row of capability tags (pill-style chips):
	•	Examples: Reasoning, Tool Use, Coding, Long Context, Multimodal
	•	Short 1–2 line description explaining what the agent or service does
	•	Metadata section with subtle typography:
	•	Environment (DEV / TEST / PROD)
	•	Agent ID / Version / Region
	•	Clear call-to-action at the bottom:
	•	Primary button (e.g., Explore, Open, Use Agent)
	•	Secondary link (e.g., Learn more →)

Visual Style:
	•	Minimal, modern, enterprise SaaS aesthetic
	•	Consistent spacing and alignment
	•	Logos or icons should immediately convey identity
	•	Tags should be color-coded but muted (no loud colors)
	•	Typography similar to AWS / Azure portals

Tone & Feel:
	•	Professional, scalable, cloud-native
	•	Should not look empty even with minimal text
	•	Cards should feel “clickable” and valuable at first glance

Use Case:
	•	AI Agent Marketplace
	•	Internal Developer Portal
	•	Model Registry / Service Catalog
